About this item

  • Polyester
  • Material: Our covers are made using Cover Max fabric, which is a 1000 denier PVC coated polyester weighing approximately 12 Oz.
  • Durability: Resistant to tears and abrasions, our covers are durable and safeguard your round table against harsh weather elements, water, UV-rays, etc., for a long time.
  • Sizes & Colors: The Round Table top covers are available in multiple sizes and colors Beige, Black, Blue, Coffee, Grey and more. You may choose from a huge range of options available.
  • Easy to Clean: The unique design and material of our covers make them easy to clean and maintain. They can be easily cleaned using water and then dried in the sun for the next use.
  • Convenient Usage: Our covers are equipped with strong and functional tie-downs for enhanced protection and easy installation & removal.

Product Description

Round Tabletop Cover (Cover Max)

The heavy-duty medium weight round tabletop cover is made of 1000 Denier PVC coated polyester. The Cover Max fall is 100% UV-resistant and waterproof material ensures protection from inclement weather and resists damage due to tears, abrasion, dust, and debris. Available in multiple sizes, the tabletop cover comes with an elastic for a snug fit and enhanced protection from the elements. Ideal for moderate weather conditions, the cover can protect the tabletop from medium adversity caused by the weather. The highly durable cover weighs approximately 12 oz and is perfect for indoor outdoor usage.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Amazon Customer
5 Stars
Simple, durable patio table cover
My cast-iron patio furniture has lived through more than a few wet California winters. I decided to buy a protective cover to protect the table this winter so I won't have to do a lot of paint and sanding touch-ups next spring.The table is 48" diameter, so I got the 54" version and it's a nice fit. The underside edge consists of four elastic sections that connect four straight sections. The result is a rather loose fit, which is fine for California but might not be as good in a windy climate.It was an inexpensive solution, and I'm happy I got it before our first storm.

l.c.r.
5.0 out of 5 stars Simple, durable patio table cover
Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2023
Size: 54" Dia x 4" HColor: BlackVerified Purchase
My cast-iron patio furniture has lived through more than a few wet California winters. I decided to buy a protective cover to protect the table this winter so I won't have to do a lot of paint and sanding touch-ups next spring.

The table is 48" diameter, so I got the 54" version and it's a nice fit. The underside edge consists of four elastic sections that connect four straight sections. The result is a rather loose fit, which is fine for California but might not be as good in a windy climate.

It was an inexpensive solution, and I'm happy I got it before our first storm.

My cast-iron patio furniture has lived through more than a few wet California winters. I decided to buy a protective cover to protect the table this winter so I won't have to do a lot of paint and sanding touch-ups next spring.

The table is 48" diameter, so I got the 54" version and it's a nice fit. The underside edge consists of four elastic sections that connect four straight sections. The result is a rather loose fit, which is fine for California but might not be as good in a windy climate.

It was an inexpensive solution, and I'm happy I got it before our first storm.

JAR63
5.0 out of 5 stars No more aggravation winterizing our table!
Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2022
Size: 60" Dia x 4" HColor: GreyVerified Purchase
We have a screened porch with a nice dining set. The first year I didnt cover the table well enough in the Fall and it got damaged during the winter. We replaced the top and since have spent some time each year covering the table top with an old blanket & enclosing with plastic sheeting and then placing the chairs on top of the table and covering the set with a patio table cover. Covering the table top with sheeting was always a dreaded and aggravating task, this year I ordered this cover so that I could eliminate using plastic sheeting and that made a 30 minute job into a 5 minute task. The cover is perfect. Nice weight (thicker & more substantial that the sheeting) and it fits beautifully over my 59 round table top and comes down around the 4 drop so everything is covered and protected from the elements. Why didnt I order one of these years ago? Glad I have one now.
